🔴 **Design Concern** — `review/arm-alertsmanagement-node.api.md:618`

```ts
export interface ProxyResource_1 {
    readonly id?: string;
    readonly name?: string;
    readonly type?: string;
}
```

The `_N` suffix (`ProxyResource_1`) is a naming collision artifact — it means TypeSpec defines two models with the same base name `ProxyResource`. In this file, `ProxyResource` already extends `Resource` (which includes `systemData`), and `ProxyResource_1` is a separate, leaner variant. Both `AlertModification` and `AlertsSummary` extend `ProxyResource_1`.

**Fix:** Open a PR in the Azure REST API spec repo to resolve the naming collision — either rename one variant using `@clientName` (e.g. `@clientName("LegacyProxyResource")`) or merge the two models into one. Then retrigger SDK generation.
